VALUES
(43, 7, 17, 43, 8, 31, 32, 'shall know of the doctrine', 'Connection of Knowledge and Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between obedience and understanding. In John 7:17, doing God''s will leads to knowledge of doctrine, while John 8:31-32 states that continuing in Jesus'' word leads to knowing the truth.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 17, 43, 8, 43, 43, 'his will', 'Understanding God''s Will', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding God''s will. In John 7:17, knowing the doctrine is linked to doing God''s will, while John 8:43 addresses the inability to hear His word, suggesting a lack of alignment with that will.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 17, 24, 31, 33, 34, 'know of the doctrine', 'Knowledge of God''s Will', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing God''s will and doctrine. Both passages emphasize that true understanding comes from an internal transformation and obedience to God''s law.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 17, 27, 12, 10, 10, NULL, 'Understanding Through Obedience', 'Both passages emphasize that understanding is linked to one''s actions and choices. John 7:17 suggests that doing God''s will leads to knowledge of doctrine, while Daniel 12:10 indicates that the wise will understand, contrasting them with the wicked who lack understanding.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 17, 50, 3, 15, 16, 'his will', 'Understanding God''s Will', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being aligned with God''s will to gain understanding. John 7:17 speaks of knowing doctrine through doing God''s will, while Philippians 3:15-16 suggests that God will reveal understanding to those who are of the same mind.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 17, 19, 25, 8, 9, 'his will', 'Divine Guidance and Understanding', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine guidance for those who seek to follow God''s will. Both passages emphasize that the Lord teaches and guides those who are willing to do His will and are meek.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 17, 19, 119, 101, 102, 'doctrine, whether it be of God', 'Connection of Obedience and Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of obedience to God''s will as a means to understand His teachings. John 7:17 suggests that doing God''s will leads to knowledge of doctrine, while Psalms 119:101-102 highlights refraining from evil to keep God''s word.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 18, 43, 5, 41, 41, 'seeketh his glory that sent him', 'Honor and Glory in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of seeking personal honor. John 7:18 highlights seeking glory from the one who sent him, while John 5:41 states, ''I receive not honour from men.''', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 18, 43, 13, 31, 32, 'seeketh his glory that sent him', 'Glory and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking glory. In John 7:18, the one who seeks the glory of the sender is true, while in John 13:31-32, Jesus speaks of being glorified by God, indicating a righteous pursuit of glory.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 18, 46, 10, 31, 33, NULL, 'Seeking Glory and Profit', 'Both passages emphasize seeking glory and profit not for oneself but for God and others. John highlights the importance of seeking the glory of the one who sent him, while Corinthians calls for actions to be done for God''s glory and the benefit of many.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 18, 50, 2, 3, 5, 'seeketh his own glory', 'Selflessness and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking the glory of others rather than one''s own. John 7:18 highlights the contrast between self-seeking and truth, while Philippians 2:3-5 encourages humility and valuing others above oneself.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 18, 40, 6, 9, 9, 'seeketh his glory that sent him', 'Seeking Glory and Hallowing Name', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking glory. In John 7:18, the focus is on seeking the glory of the one who sent him, paralleling the reverence expressed in Matthew 6:9 for God''s name.', 'theme', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 18, 52, 2, 6, 6, 'seeketh his own glory', 'Seeking Glory in Service', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of self-seeking glory. John highlights the importance of seeking the glory of the one who sent him, while Paul states they did not seek glory from men. This connection highlights a shared theme of humility in service.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 18, 20, 25, 27, 27, 'seeketh his own glory', 'Self-Glory and Its Consequences', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of seeking one''s own glory. John 7:18 highlights the truth of those who seek the glory of the one who sent them, while Proverbs 25:27 warns against the pursuit of personal glory, suggesting it lacks true value.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 19, 43, 1, 17, 17, 'Moses give you the law', 'Law and Grace Contrast', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the law given by Moses and the grace and truth brought by Jesus Christ. Both passages emphasize the significance of the law while contrasting it with the new covenant established through Christ.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 19, 40, 12, 14, 14, 'why go ye about to kill me', 'Plot Against Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the intent to kill Jesus. In John 7:19, the question of why they seek to kill him is posed, while Matthew 12:14 explicitly states that the Pharisees held a council to destroy him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 19, 43, 7, 1, 1, 'none of you keepeth the law', 'Connection of Jewish Opposition', 'Both passages emphasize the hostility towards Jesus from the Jews, with John 7:1 noting their intent to kill him and John 7:19 questioning their adherence to the law. This connection highlights the tension between Jesus and the Jewish authorities.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 19, 2, 24, 2, 3, 'Moses give you the law', 'Law and Obedience', 'This connection highlights the theme of the law given by Moses and the people''s response to it. In John 7:19, the failure to keep the law contrasts with the people''s initial commitment in Exodus 24:3 to do all the words of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 19, 5, 1, 17, 17, 'the law', 'Judgment and Law Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of law and judgment. Both passages emphasize the importance of adhering to God''s law and the impartiality required in judgment.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 19, 5, 33, 4, 4, NULL, 'Connection Between Moses and the Law', 'This connection highlights the role of Moses in delivering the law to the people. Both passages emphasize the importance of the law and the failure of the people to adhere to it.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 19, 48, 6, 13, 13, 'none of you keepeth the law', 'Law and Its Observance', 'This connection highlights the theme of failing to keep the law. Both passages emphasize that those who claim to uphold the law, whether Moses'' law or the law of circumcision, do not actually follow it.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 20, 43, 10, 20, 20, 'Thou hast a devil', 'Accusations of Madness', 'Both passages emphasize the accusation of having a devil, suggesting a shared perception of Jesus'' mental state among the people. This connection highlights the skepticism and hostility faced by Jesus during His ministry.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 20, 43, 8, 48, 48, 'hast a devil', 'Accusations of Demonic Influence', 'Both passages emphasize accusations against Jesus, labeling him as possessed. The phrase ''hast a devil'' appears in both contexts, highlighting the people''s perception of him as a threat.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 20, 41, 3, 21, 22, 'Thou hast a devil', 'Accusations of Madness and Demonic Influence', 'Both passages emphasize accusations against Jesus regarding his mental state and demonic association. In John, the people claim he has a devil, while in Mark, friends and scribes suggest he is beside himself and has Beelzebub.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 20, 41, 3, 30, 30, 'Thou hast a devil', 'Accusations of Unclean Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the accusation against Jesus regarding having a devil or unclean spirit. This connection highlights the misunderstanding and hostility Jesus faced from the people.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 20, 40, 10, 25, 25, 'thou hast a devil', 'Accusations of Demonic Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being accused of having a devil or being associated with evil. In John 7:20, the people accuse Jesus of having a devil, while in Matthew 10:25, Jesus notes that he is called Beelzebub, indicating that his followers may face similar accusations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 20, 40, 11, 18, 19, 'Thou hast a devil', 'Accusations of Demonic Influence', 'Both passages emphasize accusations of having a devil. In John, the people claim Jesus has a devil, while in Matthew, they say the same about John. This connection highlights the theme of misunderstanding and criticism faced by both figures.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 20, 44, 26, 24, 24, 'thou hast a devil', 'Accusations of Madness', 'Both passages emphasize accusations of madness directed at individuals speaking truth. In John, the people claim Jesus has a devil, while in Acts, Festus accuses Paul of being beside himself.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 21, 43, 7, 23, 23, 'I have done one work', 'Sabbath Healing and Law', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of work on the Sabbath. Jesus refers to his healing as a significant act, paralleling the necessity of circumcision on the Sabbath to uphold the law.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 21, 43, 5, 2, 11, 'I have done one work', 'Healing and Sabbath Controversy', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' miraculous healing on the Sabbath, which provokes marvel and controversy among the Jews. In John 7:21, Jesus refers to the work that causes amazement, directly linking to the healing of the impotent man in John 5:2-11.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
